senses.sense_definition: A surname of Old English origin.

examples.text: Mr. <w>Huddleston</w> has been teaching history at the college for twenty years.
The <w>Huddleston</w> family donated a large sum to the local library.

senses.sense_definition: A place name used for several unincorporated communities in the United States, such as in Arkansas, Missouri, or Virginia.

examples.text: They decided to stop in <w>Huddleston</w> to buy some supplies for the trip.
The small community of <w>Huddleston</w> is known for its quiet atmosphere.
